Looking at the skill docs again - it says:
```csharp
Assert.Contains("expected", actualString);
Assert.StartsWith("prefix", actualString);
Assert.EndsWith("suffix", actualString);
Assert.MatchesRegex(@"\d{3}-\d{4}", phoneNumber);


```

These might be available in MSTest 3.9+ or later. Let me try upgrading to a newer version. Or perhaps these are available in MSTest 4.x. Let me check what's the latest available version.

